Global Week Ahead Calendar for Dec. 10 - 17, 2011

-- B y   D i c k   S c h u m a c h e r ,   G r e g   M i l e s   a n d   J i m   M c D o n a l d
-- 
2011-12-09T15:32:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-09/global-week-ahead-calendar-for-dec-10-17-2011.html
International markets may focus on
the  Federal Reserve  and the likelihood it will maintain a zero
rates policy when the central bank’s Open Market Committee meets
on Dec. 13. Negotiations on a Greece debt swap are likely to
gain investors’ attention. The Bank of Japan will release its
quarterly business confidence survey. The  Reserve Bank  of
India may leave its rate unchanged.  Former MF Global Holdings Ltd. Chief Executive Officer Jon
Corzine follow his appearance before Congress yesterday with
testimony to a U.S. House committee. Zynga Inc. mounts an
initial public offering that will probably raise as much as $1
billion.  The Swiss National Bank may comment on its ceiling for the
euro against the franc. OPEC will probably retain its oil quota,
and Britain releases its report into the near-collapse of Royal
Bank of Scotland Group Plc. in 2008. Russia joins the  World
Trade Organization .  SATURDAY, Dec. 10  To contact the reporters on this story:
